                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/986.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 2 was timely and I have notified the Government that the
                    commissioners are coming; it accepted the notice in good part, promised its
                    publication tomorrow and pledged itself to maintain proper conditions for a free
                    ballot and free speech. Exclusive of the commissioners about thirty agents are
                    needed. The people generally are accepting our good faith but fear our
                    intentions will be defeated by duplicity.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sullivan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
